node.text:
Other women are not your competition. 

They aren’t. 

Not the girl who is is better at sports than you.
Not the girl who has the job you want.
Not the girl who has the life that sits in your mind like a dream.

Not any of those. 

Even if society tells us otherwise. 

I’ve been thinking about this a lot lately. 

One of my best friends is in town ahead of my wedding.
She’s an ex-GB athlete. 
Her ‘normal jog’ is over 15k.

And it would be easy,
So easy, 
To compare myself to her, judging my fitness with her as my measure.

I did that for a long time with other women. 
Especially where my shape, my WEIGHT, was concerned.

It was awful.
And I don’t play those games anymore. 

These days, I’d rather only compete with myself —
Setting challenges when they serve me, 
Making goals when they feel right.

And instead of viewing other women as competition,
I focus on collaboration. 

Because when one of us is stronger,
All of us are. 
Especially in a society that is desperate, SO desperate,
To get us to tear each other down. 

So today,
I just want to send a bit of love to all of you.

Here’s to empowered women.
Here’s to empowering women.

Here’s to us.

x

Kit @womensbest @womensbestwear with @ameniesseibi, shot by @chiclebelle

node.text:
The Italian’s parents have the kind of marriage I dream about. 

They’ve been together for 52 years now. 
And still when they toast, they link arms. 

When he stands up, 
He touches her face — soft, brief, just a wordless reminder of love. 

Recently he pulled out their wedding album.
In pictures they smile at each other. 

And now their house is filled with months, 
With years, 
Of photos showing the same. 

The other day, the Italian stood up. 
He touched my face — soft, brief, just a wordless reminder of love. 

And I find myself thinking how much I hope, 
That we will unfold like his parents did. 

If you, like me, 
Grew up without an example
Of how this marriage thing can work, 
How it does, sometimes, so beautifully work, 
Know this: 

It’s possible to fall in love, 
And hold that feeling forever. 

I’ve seen the proof, 
In a couple that’s clasped hands and held hearts for more than 50 years. 

I may not know the exact recipe, 
Or precisely how the path goes. 

But I know it’s possible. 

And that it’s the kind of love
Worth making real - not just dreaming about. 

x

node.text:
FAKE BEAUTY TRICKS: On a day where the news is full of how harmful social media can be, I hope videos like this help. 

I hope they remind you that it’s easy to create fake.

It’s simple to curate. 

And that it happens in a thousand ways across all our social media days. 

Like here, using an app to subtly enhance. 

I hope you know that it’s ok if your life doesn’t look like hers. 
Or your body, like hers. 

Because whatever you’re seeing,
Whatever world they’re presenting, 
May be so deliberate, perfected, perfect. 

But that you are real. 
Human, raw, complex, alive. 
And that your sheer existence 
Is a miracle. 

One far too marvellous 
To be contained on a screen. 
Caught in a filter 
Or shaped in a frame. 

x

#instavsreality #selflove #bodyconfidence

node.text:
You have the waves of the sea writ on your skin, and still you doubt your magic? 

Because you are magic. 
You are a marvel. 
You’re sun and sand and soul rolled into one, caught in the bind of a body but so much more
So very, very much more. 

I can’t stop thinking about my mom. 
About the lessons she taught me. 
About the lessons she never had a chance to learn. 

And I wonder if she knew how to love her body. 
I question it. 
She clawed and fought and sought her way to a better world. 
She struggled solo for the future of her children.

But self love. 
Did she know self love? 

Do you? 

And while I can’t speak to her, I can share this here, now. 
I can remind you as many times as I must remind myself: 

You are a force. 
You are a tumble of elements and particles and mass that somehow amass to so much more than a series of separate parts. 
You’re strength. 
You’re beauty. 
You’re greatness beyond what could ever be captured in words. 

And if you doubt,
If you forget, 
Look at yourself. 
Look at how your eyes glint like suns and your skin like seas, 
And how your soul roars with the very power of the ocean.

You are magic. 
You are a marvel. 
You are. 
You. 

x

#selflove #inspirationalquotes #poetry #stretchmarks #strengthmarks #bodyconfidence

node.text:
A juice diet didn’t change my body. 

Even though dodgy companies want you to think so. 

Even though they STEAL MY CONTENT and put fake stories behind it. 

Like this one:

Katy, a new mom. She feels insecure, unsure. So she tries the detox and BAM, her body changed so fast! 

Now she feels like herself again! 

Only Katy isn’t real. 
And the pics this company used to prove their amazing transformation? 

They’re me. Taken on the same day. Taken in the same MINUTE. Taken just to show the POWER OF ANGLES. 

Honestly, stuff like this happens all the time. 

Dodgy companies are everywhere. 
And they will LIE if it means they GET YOUR MONEY. 

So be careful with quick fixes.
Or rapid weight loss regimes. 
Be cautious with anything that promises you confidence at the end of a price tag. 

Protect yourself on here. 

And I’ll do what I can to help protect you too. 

x

#bodyconfidence #instavsreality #selflove #selfacceptance

How influencers FAKE clothing online - or let’s talk about DIGITAL FASHION. 

Digital fashion is basically like a filter for your BODY. With CLOTHES. 

It uses AR technology to dress you in real time — sort of like Cher’s closet in clueless, but a bit more real. 

Technology like this is becoming increasingly common. 

And it’s big business. 

In this app, DIGITAL (not in person, only online) looks sell for upwards of $200. 

I didn’t buy any (the cheapest were still $40), but if I did, then my pic would have been sent off to a professional retoucher. 

Those guys then make the outfit look super realistic on me. 

And bam, just like that, I’m a high fashion influencer. 

Honestly, stuff like this is pretty cool.
It’s so darn fun getting to try on lots of styles. 

But it’s also important to know that THIS IS HAPPENING. 
And it’s going to happen more and more. Apps like these are normalising the digital fashion space. 

So just keep an eye out. 
Be aware. 
Dress yourself offline or online or whatever your heart fancies. 
But remember that so much of what we see on here 
Isn’t quite ‘real’. 

x

#instavsreality #digitalfashion #socialmediavsreality #bodyconfidence

When I was 30, I got my dream job. And within two weeks of having it, the corners of my mouth started to crack. 

I was stressed. 
Exhausted. 
Waking up at 4am and sleeping at midnight and spending my weekends in the office, my life in the office. 

And my body, it was trying so hard to tell me something so simple:
Slow down. 
Breathe, darling. 
Breath before you break. 

From my Facebook group, I know I’m not the only one who does this:
Who loads the stress on,
And adds weight to an already full burden. 
Saying yes when we should say no,
And feeling a responsibility to keep going,
A shame if we stop. 

If this sounds like you,
Know this:

Your mental health matters. 
In all the ways, in all the situations, it matters. 

Balance is so critical to living this life, this ONE life, that we’ve got. 
And waking up covered in sweat,
Or skipping all things social just to keep on pushing,
That’s not healthy. 

So today, give yourself grace 
To look at your life, your goals,
And lean in to what is TRULY right for you. 

Even if it means stepping back from that project,
Or skipping that promotion,
Or cancelling on those birthday plans. 

It took me a year to hear what my body and my heart were trying to tell me.

Don’t let it take you a minute more. 

x

Photo by @chiclebelle

#selflove #bodyconfidence #worklifebalance #feminist

We have to talk about periods. Honestly. Openly. Without shame.

Because if we don’t, 
Stupidity like this holds power. 

For years, for MANY years, I was ignorant about my period. 

I lost it, when I became overly thin. 
Then I went on birth control that kept it away. 

It wasn’t until I hit my 30s that I started looking in to how my period worked. 
How it ACTUALLY worked, beyond the soft delicacy we are taught about blue dye on white cotton pads. 

I downloaded a free period tracker,
And for the first time ever, 
Started to tap into the power of my cycle. 

Now I feel increasingly strong about fighting idiocy like this. 
Because these men, who perhaps have been told almost nothing about periods their whole lives,
Are often the ones making decisions that impact ours. 

So it’s time we talked. 
Without shame. 
Without embarrassment. 
To each other. 
And to them too. 
Owning with each word, each conversation, 
The marvel that is our body. 

Period. 

x

#selflove #feminist #periods
